    "answer_id" : 7434966,
    "question_id" : 7421474,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Mix-in annotations work pretty well here as already mentioned. Another possibility beyond per-property @JsonIgnore is to use @JsonIgnoreType if you have a type that should never be included (i.e. if all instances of GeometryCollection properties should be ignored). You can then either add it directly (if you control the type), or using mix-in, like:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@JsonIgnoreType abstract class MixIn { }\n// and then register mix-in, either via SerializationConfig, or by using SimpleModule\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This can be more convenient if you have lots of classes that all have a single 'IgnoredType getContext()' accessor or so (which is the case for many frameworks)</p>\n"
  }, {
